Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.66,0:01:38.41,Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have given birth to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.71,0:01:49.59,Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Who would you be sold to, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:52.09,Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you weren't interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.09,0:01:54.30,Flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't handle pain very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:56.97,Flashback,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I should at least be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:58.60,Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.60,0:02:01.39,Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:06.77,Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, you didn't care whether \Nyou lived or died, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:47.19,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:52.69,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:55.53,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:02:58.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,G-Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.04,0:03:04.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.41,0:03:07.42,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She's a neighbor that lives\Nhere. Her name is Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.17,0:03:13.34,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She's a fairy who does the cooking and \Nlaundry, cleans and tends to the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:16.51,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Silky prepared that, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.22,0:03:24.06,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You could say she's less of\N a servant and more of a landlady.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.28,0:03:38.03,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,A little something for my acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:44.12,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, I was purchased\Nby this mage for an outrageous sum.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:49.15,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,As his apprentice, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:53.79,Flashback,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I also hope to make you my bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.76,0:03:57.38,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Apprentice or bride...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.38,0:03:59.76,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Which do I take seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.43,0:04:03.22,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You've been asleep for two\Ndays. Do you recall anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:04.47,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Two days?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:06.77,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You must have been emotionally exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:13.36,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His appearance, his mannerisms... \NI don't understand him very well yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:14.98,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.90,0:04:24.58,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But he's going to take care of me, so \Nhe's not a bad person... I don't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:32.83,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to bring this up to you \Nso early in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:36.75,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,but shall we prepare for our honeymoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.05,0:04:44.26,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,But... he's seems pretty weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.53,0:05:02.82,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd introduce you to my \Nacquaintances while we go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.99,0:05:06.66,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His face is bone, so I can't \Nread his expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:09.50,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell when he's serious or kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:14.67,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What happened to your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:18.42,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I would look suspicious wandering \Naround outside with that head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:22.13,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I used a little magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:24.26,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:27.18,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,It feels different to the touch, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.31,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look good?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.31,0:05:29.14,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Am I handsome?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:34.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You look kind of fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:37.36,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:41.40,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I come here often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.99,0:05:44.78,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find almost all \Nyour equipment here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:49.87,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Is this place open?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:53.12,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,This is just for show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.21,0:05:55.37,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Angie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.37,0:05:56.50,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Angelica.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.13,0:06:00.92,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Ainsworth!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:05.34,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Who would have thought you'd \Never come out of your hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:09.18,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You're no less of a hermit, Gem's Bee.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.18,0:06:11.60,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm running a business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:12.52,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.52,0:06:13.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.85,0:06:20.40,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd have you gather \Nthe things this girl needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.45,0:06:27.53,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I made her my apprentice three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.08,0:06:31.58,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,A-Apprentice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.29,0:06:33.16,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.25,0:06:36.71,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.71,0:06:38.38,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,From Japan, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:40.13,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:41.88,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:44.13,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:45.76,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,She's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.26,0:06:49.18,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You better not have done\N anything shady to get her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.10,0:06:52.68,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The money I bought her with was clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:55.02,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing proper about {\i1}buying{\i0} her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:57.31,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't done anything \Nweird to you, has he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.31,0:06:59.48,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.73,0:07:01.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Anything weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:06.20,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, Chise, you need to \Nbe quicker to deny that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.20,0:07:11.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He washed me after taking off my clothes,\N and he proposed to me... Does that count?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:12.95,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:19.08,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You perverted mage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:21.42,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Go take a walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:26.38,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have a smidge of common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.69,0:07:41.90,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Man, so that Ainsworth \Nfound an apprentice, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.23,0:07:45.28,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Did he really propose?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.45,0:07:49.11,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.07,0:07:54.58,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I forgot to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.37,0:07:57.54,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Angelica Burley.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.54,0:08:00.50,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a mage, which are a dying breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:02.63,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a magus craft artificer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:04.88,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Magus craft?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.13,0:08:10.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Tools and contraptions that run \Non magic instead of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.84,0:08:13.60,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Processing gems, making knives...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.35,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I do it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.35,0:08:16.29,Default,Alucia,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.06,0:08:19.31,Default,Alucia,0000,0000,0000,,A visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:20.60,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Althea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:23.02,Default,Alucia,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:26.28,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but we're putting that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.28,0:08:28.36,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Stay quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.57,0:08:33.66,Default,Alucia,0000,0000,0000,,You promised you'd watch my training!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.66,0:08:35.37,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,All right, just scram!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.50,0:08:41.12,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Was that your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.12,0:08:42.00,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:43.83,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, she's not very well-behaved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.25,0:08:50.09,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,For better or worse, she's got what \Nit takes to become a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.68,0:08:54.97,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'd prefer that she'd take up a proper \Njob, especially in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:08:59.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.15,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Has Elias not told you yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:06.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:09.99,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,There's magic and sorcery in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.99,0:09:11.90,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know the difference between the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.16,0:09:18.20,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,To put it simply, sorcerers\Nemploy a science called "sorcery."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:20.20,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,They have an understanding of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:25.33,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,and they use their own power to rewrite \Nit and change it to their own ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.34,0:09:34.68,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, the magic that we mages use \Nrefers to the miracles that are caused
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.68,0:09:38.81,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,with the help of fairies and spirits, \Ntheir powers bending said reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.81,0:09:40.18,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:44.06,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Magic sounds easier, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:49.61,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,But it's like having someone be your arms \Nand legs, so it's hard to regulate and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.61,0:09:53.40,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Should you try to do more than \Nwhat you're capable of...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:10:01.12,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I made a silly mistake during my training,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:02.20,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,so that's what I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:06.13,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot to study \Nwhen it comes to magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:09.67,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You have to take it seriously, \Nor this is what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.67,0:10:11.38,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,So make sure you study hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:25.23,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Can I use magic, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:28.27,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you give it a try?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.32,0:10:30.30,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.49,0:10:42.79,Default,Hugo,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.79,0:10:45.02,Default,Hugo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm loyal to Angelica,\Nso I can't promise to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.02,0:10:47.54,Default,Hugo,0000,0000,0000,,my kindest to you, \Nbut nice to meet you anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:52.51,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,This is Hugo, my familiar. \NA vodyanoy water spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.51,0:10:55.09,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,He's mischievous, but he's hard-working.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:58.34,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Hugo, give her a hand, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.34,0:11:00.10,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,She needs to practice magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.43,0:11:03.43,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.48,0:11:07.90,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,There's a first time for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:13.73,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be using that for practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:17.15,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Will it to take on a shape of your choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:19.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Will it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:20.37,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:23.29,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Think of your favorite flower, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:28.17,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.92,0:11:31.21,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Air is hot water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:33.25,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You, yourself, are pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:36.01,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Therein, the crystal forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.51,0:11:38.16,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Picture that in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.98,0:11:52.06,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What is my favorite flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.41,0:12:02.91,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,When? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.96,0:12:15.84,Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.67,0:12:19.47,Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's a flower garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:20.68,Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,How pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.72,0:12:25.22,Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,How pretty, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.47,0:12:26.22,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.65,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Angelica.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.65,0:12:36.40,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go teaching my apprentice things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.27,0:12:39.57,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:51.58,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.58,0:12:52.50,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:54.00,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Ainsworth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.38,0:12:56.34,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,What is that young lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:12.10,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.65,0:13:14.15,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,but it isn't omnipotent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.23,0:13:17.61,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She's a Sleigh Beggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.82,0:13:24.45,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.91,0:13:26.62,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:28.91,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,The less people know, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.75,0:13:33.92,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.84,0:13:37.80,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Hugo!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.80,0:13:38.96,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:40.75,Default,Hugo,0000,0000,0000,,No, well, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.05,0:13:43.72,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,She's a special existence to the fairies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.14,0:13:51.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.56,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I made a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.36,0:14:01.11,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:05.45,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, it's that bonehead's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.45,0:14:07.24,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,That shithead who didn't tell us anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:08.08,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Shithead?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:11.91,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't explain things to your \Napprentice, you're nothing but a shithead!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:17.00,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, would you do me a favor and get \Nme the broom and hammer in the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:17.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:20.50,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you, Ains?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:27.55,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm charging you extra.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:34.81,Default,Angie,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:36.48,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.52,0:14:42.99,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,An ocean alloy knife forged with \Nthe nectar of a crystal moonflower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:45.74,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,An overcoat woven from thunderbird feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.74,0:14:50.58,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What else? Glashtyn hide, a belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:55.00,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll throw in some steelvine\Nstring and a fluorite loupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.50,0:16:21.75,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,So you like poppies, Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:26.80,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I actually "like" them.\N It's just something I remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:30.09,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a flower garden like \Nthat a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:34.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,With my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:41.48,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Are your parents dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.02,0:16:43.86,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Or did they abandon you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.32,0:16:46.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty blunt, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.90,0:16:50.25,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,However your past or \Nupbringing may have been,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:53.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,it makes no difference regarding \Nthe fact that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.54,0:16:59.08,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.75,0:17:08.38,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,His plain, dispassionate words \Nare somehow comforting and kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.22,0:17:19.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what my father \Nis doing, but my mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.19,0:17:24.69,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,She died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.57,0:17:29.28,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,In front of my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.20,0:17:32.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:44.17,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.17,0:17:45.75,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Ainsworth!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:50.30,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I write back to you saying \NI'd be here around now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:53.47,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you take off just\N as I was getting here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.47,0:17:54.84,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to be a hermit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.84,0:17:56.85,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I have things to do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.85,0:18:00.14,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Your servants hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.14,0:18:02.31,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,They won't even let me in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.31,0:18:05.77,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to bother coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:12.07,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Chise, his new apprentice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.99,0:18:14.24,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.24,0:18:15.78,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:17.33,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Simon Cullum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.87,0:18:21.45,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here today to ask you two to \Ndo a bit of an errand for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.09,0:18:33.34,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I waited outside for two whole hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:38.22,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Simon is the priest at the village church.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:44.35,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Although, he does sermons both as a priest \Nand as a pastor, so he sits on the fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.35,0:18:46.48,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Call me "studious."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:49.02,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to be tense, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:51.26,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Simon is just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:56.82,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am but a pitiful lamb, cowering \Nin fear of the terrible mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:57.53,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.53,0:18:59.16,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,You pull no punches.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.95,0:19:02.04,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,They don't get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:03.50,Magus-top,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,It's still cold outside, even \Nthough it's almost summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:04.91,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias is especially spiteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:07.38,Magus-top,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,You could have gone back to \Nchurch and come tomorrow, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:06.54,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Silky, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.38,0:19:10.54,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a pain in the butt, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:15.63,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Chise-kun, I think I understand \Nyour situation, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:18.05,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.55,0:19:22.81,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to come to my church if \Nyou ever get sick of this bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.81,0:19:24.31,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hear you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.31,0:19:25.31,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.85,0:19:27.94,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.78,0:19:37.45,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't something we can deal \Nwith, but it should be easy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:39.28,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Three?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.28,0:19:39.95,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.45,0:19:43.54,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,It's a penalty for your free actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.33,0:19:49.96,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,You've been silent for decades, and now \Nyou've suddenly taken an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.96,0:19:52.71,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any option but \Nto report to the brass.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.71,0:19:56.63,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think of myself as \Nbeing managed by the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.63,0:19:57.88,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:00.01,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not bother with this, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.34,0:20:06.35,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want to mess with you mages\Nwho have already lived longer than we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:12.06,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,How many centuries is it going to take \Nbefore your superiors rethink their ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:17.15,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,If only God or his son would \Nwrite us a letter or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:21.87,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because I'm here that \Nyou have to bother with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.45,0:20:24.83,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,It's absolutely not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.29,0:20:28.00,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,We have all kinds of nasty issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:32.54,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,May I have the usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.54,0:20:33.38,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:40.84,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,I heal all the people of this village with\N the medicine that Ainsworth makes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:47.14,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Should you learn magic and use it to craft \Nmedicines, they will work miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:51.48,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,The medicine of a mage is \Neffective and gentle to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:55.61,Default,Simon,0000,0000,0000,,Study well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:21:01.03,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't believe he'd think highly \Nof you, being that he's a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:02.10,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Does he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:05.70,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Britain is a land of ancient magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.08,0:21:09.62,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Mages are an important \Npart of life here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:12.50,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Chise,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.92,0:21:18.55,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,why don't we go on our honeymoon \Nwhile we run our errands?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.92,0:21:23.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't kidding about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.44,0:21:36.52,Magus-internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Iceland, a volcanic island \Nin the Arctic Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:42.36,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that the dragons \Nare on the move lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.91,0:21:44.62,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I've been asked to check on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.19,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.87,0:21:54.50,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.55,0:22:09.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He's still not very careful, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.68,0:22:13.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't even hold \Nonto his own apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.44,0:22:15.73,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.15,0:22:19.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We shall discuss that at our own land.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.48,0:22:24.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,At the last land of the dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.77,0:23:57.07,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The two are torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:24:00.49,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Death and life intertwine \Nat the ends of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.90,0:24:05.54,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What does the girl see when the \Ndoor to her memories are opened?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.85,0:24:09.04,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, little sorceress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.04,0:24:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
